    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "When "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "compute_uv"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is True, the result is a namedtuple with the following\nattribute names: "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "U"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "S"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Vh"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The decomposition is performed using LAPACK routine "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "_gesdd"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "SVD is usually described for the factorization of a 2D matrix "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "A"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ".\nThe higher-dimensional case will be discussed below. In the 2D case, SVD is\nwritten as "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "A = U S V^H"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", where "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "A = a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "U= u"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ",\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "S= \\mathtt{fnp.diag}(s)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "V^H = vh"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ". The 1D array "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "s"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "\ncontains the singular values of "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "u"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "vh"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " are unitary. The rows\nof "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "vh"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " are the eigenvectors of "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "A^H A"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and the columns of "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "u"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " are\nthe eigenvectors of "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "A A^H"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ". In both cases the corresponding\n(possibly non-zero) eigenvalues are given by "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "s**2"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "If "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " has more than two dimensions, then broadcasting rules apply, as\nexplained in "
            },
            {
              "display_text": "routines.linalg-broadcasting",
              "explicit_title": false,
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "",
              "kind": "role_reference",
              "original_target": "routines.linalg-broadcasting",
              "role": "ref",
              "suppress_link": false,
              "target": "routines.linalg-broadcasting",
              "unresolved": true
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ". This means that SVD is\nworking in \"stacked\" mode: it iterates over all indices of the first\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a.ndim - 2"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " dimensions and for each combination SVD is applied to the\nlast two indices. The matrix "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " can be reconstructed from the\ndecomposition with either "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "(u * s[..., None, :]) @ vh"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " or\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "u @ (s[..., None] * vh)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ". (The "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "@"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " operator can be replaced by the\nfunction "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/matmul",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "matmul",
              "text": "fnp.matmul"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " for python versions below 3.5.)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "If "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is a "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "matrix"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " object (as opposed to an "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "ndarray"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "), then so are\nall the return values."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import flopscope as fnp"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "rng = fnp.random.default_rng()"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "a = rng.normal(size=(9, 6)) + 1j*rng.normal(size=(9, 6))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "b = rng.normal(size=(2, 7, 8, 3)) + 1j*rng.normal(size=(2, 7, 8, 3))"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Reconstruction based on full SVD, 2D case:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "U, S, Vh = fnp.linalg.svd(a, full_matrices=True)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "U.shape, S.shape, Vh.shape"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "((9, 9), (6,), (6, 6))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "fnp.allclose(a, fnp.dot(U[:, :6] * S, Vh))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "True"
            },
            {
